<<> Kali laughted as if she had heard a joke "Cowards won't survive in 
> Predacon's world"said Kali"and neither in BlackFortress... Under the 
> command of Darkfate you can be fool... but not coward... That's true as my 
> name is Kali "Kali did a smile she knew that she had lost the bot but she 
> liked to stay one second more, she knew that Azure was using diplomatic 
> methods, that meant that she would be safe at least while she dind't 
> pressed so much"So, Maximal,  did you went to Pred's territory, didn't 
> you????? that's very brave; I should admit it, not all bots would do 
> that... why did you go, anyway???" >>

Mistra felt somewhat more relaxed...this Kali didn't seem like she was going 
to attack them. Of course, she'd keep her guard up. She understood bits and 
pieces of what exactly Kali was saying, but the rest was beyond her. Soon or 
later she'd know..she'd have to if she wanted to be of any help. 

The last thing Kali said registered, although Mistra didn't know the 
circumstances...so, Azure had gone into Predicon territory then? Still, the 
word 'brave' seemed to fit the large transmetal dragon. Her ears flicked as 
the Predicon finished talking. "Might I ask...why he should have to explain 
his actions to you?"

--part1_126.b85fae1.2996cbea_boundary
